Program: Discovery
Title: First Technology - crops
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry31
Last Broadcast Date: 22 May 2002
How the Neolithic revolution changed the course of mankind's future. Just over 15,000 years ago humans were a sparse population of hunter-gatherers. The the Neolithic revolution, which brought with it the advent of agriculture changed everything. Subsequently the global population rising from 10 million to 6 billion over 500 generations. Show less